## Quickstart

Get started with Moon in 5 simple steps:

### 1. Create a collection

```bash
curl -X POST "{{.BaseURL}}{{.Prefix}}/collections:create" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"name":"products","columns":[{"name":"title","type":"string","nullable":false},{"name":"price","type":"float","nullable":false}]}'
```

### 2. Insert a record

```bash
curl -X POST "{{.BaseURL}}{{.Prefix}}/{collection}:create" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"data":{"title":"Laptop","price":999.99}}'
```

### 3. List records

```bash
curl -s "{{.BaseURL}}{{.Prefix}}/{collection}:list" | jq .
```

### 4. Update a record

```bash
curl -X POST "{{.BaseURL}}{{.Prefix}}/{collection}:update" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"id":"01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FBX","data":{"price":899.99}}'
```

### 5. Delete a record

```bash
curl -X POST "{{.BaseURL}}{{.Prefix}}/{collection}:destroy" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"id":"01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FBX"}'
```

